  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nThe Retry annotation from smallrye-fault-tolerance marks methods that should be called again if an exception of a certain type are thrown. One can define that type with the retryOn field of the annotation, or with a global property Retry/retryOn.\r\n\r\nPB with the latter is that it is not compatible with native build, where we end up in a ClassNotFoundException.\r\n\r\nI have a reproducer.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo exception when executing the microservice using smallrye-fault-tolerance.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nClassNotFoundException because of the listed Exceptions in the property list value have not been retained by the native-image compiler.\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\n[retry-on-annotation-native-incompat-reproducer.zip](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/files/8880675/retry-on-annotation-native-incompat-reproducer.zip)\r\n\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\n5.13.0-48-generic #54~20.04.1-Ubuntu\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\n$ java -version openjdk version \"11.0.15\" 2022-04-19 OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 11.0.15+10-Ubuntu-0ubuntu0.20.04.1) OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM (build 11.0.15+10-Ubuntu-0ubuntu0.20.04.1, mixed mode, sharing)\n\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\n\ngraalvm-ce-java17-21.3.0\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n2.9.2.Final\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\nApache Maven 3.8.5\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
